<br>
The most measurable example I've been able to come up with was at  a PoJ execution trial I was helping someone with last night.  Like most people I've probably done this more than 10 times.  This time, I was consistently taking agro from a 65 warrior with draught of E'ci.  I have subtlety 3, been playing this game more than 3 years, and I just don't see how I should be getting more agro than the warrior by casting a draught when the mob is at 85. <br>
<br>
I dunno, maybe I get more trigger happy as my mana pool grows, but I really feel there was a palpable change since last week's patch.<br>
